The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Asian Paints shines bright 

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Jan. 19: Asian Paints has registered a rise of around 21 per cent in net profit for the quarter ended December 31 at Rs 50.11 crore compared with Rs 41.51 crore in the corresponding period last fiscal.

 The net sales of the company increased by 32 per cent to Rs 595.95 crore from Rs 451.07 crore in the year-ago period. The profit before depreciation, interest and tax (PBDIT) for the quarter increased by 27 per cent to Rs 99.04 crore from Rs 78.19 crore. Profit before tax and extraordinary item was Rs 86.07 crore compared with Rs 64.75 crore, an increase of 33 per cent.

 Vice-chairman and managing director Ashwin Dani said, ?The company has registered good growth in decorative coatings as all product segments did well. The performance of industrial coatings has been excellent mainly because of good performance in automotive and protective coatings segment.?

 ?Raw material prices rose sharply during the quarter. However, measures taken in sourcing and better management of overheads have enabled the company to mitigate pressure on margins to a large extent. In December, the company has effected a price increase of around 4.5 per cent to partially offset the increase in material costs,? added Dani.

 For the nine months ended December 31, Asian Paints has posted an increase of 13 per cent at Rs 132.38 crore against Rs 117.23 crore in the corresponding period of the previous financial year.

 For the same period, the net sales of the company increased by almost 17 per cent to Rs 1,545.57 crore from Rs 1325.6 crore in the year-ago period.

 The company?s PBDIT was Rs 255.34 crore compared with Rs 222.87 crore, an increase of almost 15 per cent. 

 Profit before tax and extraordinary item was Rs 216.83 crore compared with Rs 182.6 crore, an increase of 19 per cent.




